   ]

     "shell.execute_reply": "2023-11-06T09:01:33.988274Z"

   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "np.random.seed(123)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "dbef25ef-44e0-4d35-bfa4-5be3bb3a393e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "In this tutorial, we are going to demonstrate some forms of parameters recovery, prior predictive and posterior predictive sampling that can be a way to assess the strength of the model fitting."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a3a79141-eeda-47fa-bff1-eecd6bf035ee",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Continuous HGF\n",
    "### Simulate a dataset"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "70400fe9-3277-4674-97de-d17543d42054",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2023-11-06T09:01:33.992686Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2023-11-06T09:01:33.992434Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2023-11-06T09:01:34.048552Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2023-11-06T09:01:34.046694Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "n_data = 6\n",
    "dataset = []\n",
    "for participant in range(n_data):\n",
    "    input_data = []\n",
    "    kappa_1 = 1.0\n",
    "    omega_1 = -10.0\n",
    "    omega_2 = -10.0\n",
    "    mu_1 = 0.0\n",
    "    mu_2 = 0.0\n",
    "    pi_1 = 1e4\n",
    "    pi_2 = 1e1\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # two-level hierarchical gaussian random walk\n",
    "    for i in range(1000):\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # x2\n",
    "        pi_2 = np.exp(omega_2)\n",
    "        mu_2 = np.random.normal(mu_2, pi_2**.5)\n",
    "\n",
    "        # x1\n",
    "        pi_1 = np.exp(kappa_1 * mu_2 + omega_1)\n",
    "        mu_1 = np.random.normal(mu_1, pi_1**.5)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # input node\n",
    "        u = np.random.normal(mu_1, 1e-4**.5)\n",
    "        input_data.append(u)\n",
    "\n",
    "    dataset.append(np.array(input_data))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "05113abe-28f8-4dce-916a-7ec7610ab080",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2023-11-06T09:01:34.053819Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2023-11-06T09:01:34.053324Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2023-11-06T09:01:34.345012Z",

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",

   "metadata": {
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "## Embedding a serie of HGFs in a graphical model"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0edda7e6-6cae-4fd3-841b-16b985b7635e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Here, we are goingin to estimate the parameter $omega_{1}$ from the time series created by the hierarchical random walks. All the time series were generated using $omega_{1} = -10.0$ and we want to see how the Bayesian inference can retrieve these values."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "70824c5b-3800-48f6-b8f6-f2f2a2bf1307",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2023-11-06T09:01:34.349573Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2023-11-06T09:01:34.349184Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2023-11-06T09:01:34.355596Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2023-11-06T09:01:34.354361Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "hgf_logp_op = HGFDistribution(\n",
    "    n_levels=2,\n",
    "    model_type=\"continuous\",\n",
    "    input_data=dataset,\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "0c79400e-fadf-485e-a5e8-52fe86db13b5",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2023-11-06T09:01:34.360694Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2023-11-06T09:01:34.360080Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2023-11-06T09:01:34.847397Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2023-11-06T09:01:34.845911Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "with pm.Model() as model:\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Priors\n",
    "    # ------\n",
    "    tonic_volatility_1 = pm.Normal(\"omega_1\", mu=0.0, sigma=2.0, shape=n_data)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # The multi-HGF distribution\n",
    "    # --------------------------\n",
    "    pm.Potential(\"hgf_loglike\", hgf_logp_op(tonic_volatility_1=tonic_volatility_1, tonic_volatility_2=-10.0))"
   ]
  },
